The paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques to classify sleep signals, which is a problem in the field of signal processing and biomedical engineering. However, the focus of the paper is on comparing different unsupervised feature extractors and sequence-based classifiers, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image processing techniques (e.g., Deep Belief Networks), which could place it in the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing techniques (e.g., Conditional Random Fields), which could place it in the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
